00:13:14.610 --> 00:13:17.580
He has used his scholarly
agenda to describe

00:13:17.580 --> 00:13:21.120
how students with disabilities
got to Harvard, how

00:13:21.120 --> 00:13:23.430
do you achieve the mountain,
and what things went

00:13:23.430 --> 00:13:24.930
into achieving the
mountain and what

00:13:24.930 --> 00:13:26.857
lessons we can learn from it.

00:13:26.857 --> 00:13:28.440
But for the students
with disabilities

00:13:28.440 --> 00:13:31.550
who we have across
the university,

00:13:31.550 --> 00:13:35.450
if they happen to be unfortunate
enough to have my class,

00:13:35.450 --> 00:13:40.460
will tell me, you know,
I've had Tom Hehir's class.

00:13:40.460 --> 00:13:44.210
You are, you've been a
conspirator, a friend.

00:13:44.210 --> 00:13:47.240
I have enormously enjoyed so
much when we do home and away

00:13:47.240 --> 00:13:50.780
visits in our classes, and
our regular conferences

00:13:50.780 --> 00:13:53.390
between HPOD Harvard
Project on disability

00:13:53.390 --> 00:13:56.060
and Harvard Graduate
School of Education,

00:13:56.060 --> 00:13:58.790
and we're not going
to let you retire.

00:13:58.790 --> 00:14:01.760
We're not possibly
letting you retire.

00:14:01.760 --> 00:14:06.300
Our keynote, Dr. Judith Human
doesn't need an introduction,

00:14:06.300 --> 00:14:09.440
but she'll get one anyway.

00:14:09.440 --> 00:14:11.540
One of the most
well-respected, well

00:14:11.540 --> 00:14:16.040
traveled, well-known disability
rights advocates in the world,

00:14:16.040 --> 00:14:18.680
literally, without exaggeration.

00:14:18.680 --> 00:14:20.480
If you wanted to look
at home and trace

00:14:20.480 --> 00:14:23.000
the arc of the American
disability rights movement,

00:14:23.000 --> 00:14:26.120
you would begin with Berkeley
and the independent living

00:14:26.120 --> 00:14:30.140
movement, the sit-ins
in San Francisco

00:14:30.140 --> 00:14:34.220
to enact the 504 regulations
to have them released,

00:14:34.220 --> 00:14:35.990
the Americans with
Disabilities Act,

00:14:35.990 --> 00:14:38.540
the Individuals with
Disabilities Education Act

00:14:38.540 --> 00:14:42.080
is reauthorized, and by
the way, as undersecretary

00:14:42.080 --> 00:14:45.020
for education the implementer
and the thinker around how

00:14:45.020 --> 00:14:48.380
to put in those regulations, and
how to get the Supreme Court's

00:14:48.380 --> 00:14:52.040
decision in Raleigh, which said
basically any old education is

00:14:52.040 --> 00:14:52.840
fine.

00:14:52.840 --> 00:14:56.240
They actually mean, no, we want
to make sure that all kids have

00:14:56.240 --> 00:14:57.710
their full potential.

00:14:57.710 --> 00:14:59.300
And move forward
to the convention

00:14:59.300 --> 00:15:01.720
on the Rights of Persons
with Disabilities,

00:15:01.720 --> 00:15:03.860
where I was privileged
to sit-in the corner

00:15:03.860 --> 00:15:07.760
in the back with Judy and
Charlotte and Cheri and others,

00:15:07.760 --> 00:15:09.740
where I learned
so much about her.

00:15:09.740 --> 00:15:12.290
What you don't have in
this booklet, is this

00:15:12.290 --> 00:15:19.370
is the leader, den mother,
icon, example, talkless talker

00:15:19.370 --> 00:15:23.900
for generations of disability
rights advocates and scholars.

00:15:23.900 --> 00:15:26.180
She has been the older
sister to most of us

00:15:26.180 --> 00:15:29.060
in learning about disability
rights advocacy, and the person

00:15:29.060 --> 00:15:31.370
who has set the
example for those of us

00:15:31.370 --> 00:15:33.360
who spend our lives
reading, writing,

00:15:33.360 --> 00:15:37.670
and advocating on behalf of
persons with disabilities.

00:15:37.670 --> 00:15:40.860
Judy is respected and
adored around the world,

00:15:40.860 --> 00:15:44.510
and I echo and include
Cheri and everyone else here

00:15:44.510 --> 00:15:47.120
to say you are
appreciated and loved.

00:15:47.120 --> 00:15:50.300
So thank you so much
for all that you do.

00:15:50.300 --> 00:15:53.450
We'll please ask the
discussant and the keynote

00:15:53.450 --> 00:15:56.177
to come forward.

00:15:56.177 --> 00:16:13.465
[APPLAUSE]

